**English:**
10 Accursed be you, ancient she-wolf, 11 who more than all other beasts are ravenous 12 for your insatiable hunger!
13 O heavens, in whose revolutions it seems to be believed 14 that the conditions down here can be changed, 15 when will he come for whom this [she-wolf] will depart?
